WEBVTT

00:14.765 --> 00:17.848
ANTOINE: But, no, you see,
you took two sides of the triangle, brah.

00:17.935 --> 00:21.268
Carrollton to Esplanade, what you needed to
do was just go down the one side.

00:21.355 --> 00:22.686
-What?
-C|aiborne.

00:22.773 --> 00:25.150
Claiborne is the hypotenuse
of the triangle, see?

00:25.234 --> 00:26.189
What?

00:26.277 --> 00:28.643
The hypotenuse of the triangle that we was in.

00:28.738 --> 00:31.605
Give me my $16, stop talking bullshit, huh?

00:31.699 --> 00:33.860
lt's basic geometry, brah.

00:33.951 --> 00:36.488
New Orleans is crescent-shaped,
like a triangle.

00:36.579 --> 00:38.035
Now, you need to get with the hypotenuse.

00:38.122 --> 00:41.364
Now, don't believe me, believe Pythagoras.
He made a science of this shit.

00:41.459 --> 00:43.996
I owe you 10, tip included. Shit.

00:44.086 --> 00:47.874
I'm about ready to pay you 10
just to have you shut the fuck up.

00:47.965 --> 00:49.250
(CHUCKLES)

00:49.342 --> 00:51.128
(MUSICIANS PLAYING)

01:05.650 --> 01:07.390
(SINGING) One glad morning

01:07.485 --> 01:10.192
When this life is over

01:10.279 --> 01:13.066
l'll fly away

01:14.492 --> 01:18.610
When I die
Hallelujah by and by

01:19.413 --> 01:22.997
l'll fly away

01:27.922 --> 01:30.083
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:34.011 --> 01:37.469
OFFICER 1: That's it! Stop the music!
OFFICER 2: No more!

01:37.556 --> 01:40.093
Hold it! Stop, no more!

01:40.184 --> 01:42.766
-That's it! No more music! Break it up!
-(MUS|C STOPS)

01:42.853 --> 01:45.344
OFFICER 3: There's no Jazz Fest.
Shut them down.

01:45.439 --> 01:47.600
This is a memorial for my little brother.
Come on, now.

01:47.692 --> 01:49.603
We got noise complaints.

01:49.694 --> 01:51.810
This a memorial for Ken/vin James, man.

01:51.904 --> 01:54.486
-Y'a|| can't be playing your instruments...
-MAN 1: Arrested my cousin, man.

01:54.573 --> 01:57.110
-...out here without a permit.
-WOMAN: Yeah.

01:57.201 --> 02:00.113
All right.
Y'all can't stop us from singing, right?

02:00.204 --> 02:02.661
We can sing in the streets, right?

02:02.748 --> 02:04.704
One glad morning

02:04.792 --> 02:07.784
When this life is over
I'll...

02:07.878 --> 02:09.163
MAN 1: Sing!

02:09.255 --> 02:10.370
Fly away

02:11.507 --> 02:16.217
When I die
Hallelujah by and by...

02:16.304 --> 02:17.669
WOMAN: Come on, now!

02:17.763 --> 02:20.300
l'll fly away

02:20.391 --> 02:24.054
Oh, |'|| fly away

02:24.145 --> 02:25.430
Fly away.

02:25.521 --> 02:29.685
Oh, glory, l'll fly away

02:29.775 --> 02:32.482
MAN 1: Come on, man!
OFFICER 1: Let's go!

02:33.237 --> 02:34.852
MAN 1: We didn't do nothing, man!

02:34.947 --> 02:36.562
(CROWD YELLING)

02:39.577 --> 02:40.987
OFFICER 1: Come on, let's go!

02:41.078 --> 02:43.455
Y'all just don't get it! Y'all just don't get it!

02:48.502 --> 02:50.993
MAN 1: It don't make no sense.

02:51.130 --> 02:53.337
-It don't make no sense.
-WOMAN: We ain't doing nothing.

02:53.424 --> 02:56.006
-Man, this is bullshit.
-What was that?

02:56.093 --> 02:59.381
Look, I'm just saying.
Ken/Vin James was a loved man,

02:59.472 --> 03:02.179
and we all played music with him
at one point or another.

03:02.266 --> 03:03.927
We told you. We got complaints.

03:04.018 --> 03:06.009
Anybody with complaints
about music in Treme,

03:06.103 --> 03:08.845
-they in the wrong place altogether.
-ALL: Yeah.

03:08.939 --> 03:10.520
Clear the streets!

03:10.608 --> 03:12.815
Come on, man. We here out of respect!

03:13.527 --> 03:17.019
-l'm telling you, clear the area.
-MAN 1: This is bullshit.

03:17.114 --> 03:19.446
MAN 1: Are you serious?
MAN 2: We can't celebrate his life.

03:19.533 --> 03:21.615
OFFICER 1: Wrap it up, folks! Let's go!

03:23.788 --> 03:26.700
Come on, keep going! Keep going!

03:28.000 --> 03:29.615
All right, party's over!

03:29.710 --> 03:31.325
Let's go! Good night!

03:31.420 --> 03:33.251
OFFICER 1: Party's over!
OFFICER 2: Let's go, people!

03:33.339 --> 03:35.500
(VOCALIZING)

03:36.467 --> 03:37.957
(CAR APPROACHING)

03:47.311 --> 03:49.222
MAN OVER RADIO: 120.
WOMAN OVER RADIO: 120.

03:49.730 --> 03:51.061
-Respect, huh?
-(HANDCUFFS CLlNKlNG)

03:51.148 --> 03:53.400
WOMAN OVER RADIO:
Any more units out there?

03:53.484 --> 03:55.896
MAN OVER RADIO:
Negative, it's under control, copy?

03:55.986 --> 03:57.317
WOMAN OVER RADIO: Copy, over.

05:37.713 --> 05:39.328
Ah, fuck!

05:39.423 --> 05:42.005
I gotta start my show in, like, 15 minutes.

05:42.468 --> 05:44.083
We'll catch a tune or two.

05:44.178 --> 05:46.715
Yeah, it's her New Orleans debut.
I wanted to see it.

05:46.805 --> 05:49.262
-Check, check. One, two...
-Yes.

05:49.350 --> 05:52.308
Okay, we are Annie T.
and the Bayou St. John Playboys.

05:52.394 --> 05:53.349
(CROWD APPLAUDS)

05:53.437 --> 05:55.018
At least that's what
we're going with right now,

05:55.105 --> 05:57.391
so check back in a week or so.

05:58.317 --> 05:59.807
(BAND PLAYING)

06:11.163 --> 06:14.030
(SINGING) Nothin' ever comes
from out of nowhere

06:14.124 --> 06:16.866
Ain't nobody ever rides for free

06:16.961 --> 06:19.873
There's a hundred million
heartaches out there

06:19.964 --> 06:22.626
Between the devil and the deep blue sea

06:22.716 --> 06:25.128
And all the troubles of the wide world flow

06:25.302 --> 06:28.590
Down the Mississippi to the Gulf of Mexico

06:30.599 --> 06:32.635
Here it comes again

06:33.727 --> 06:35.718
Ready or not

06:36.522 --> 06:38.888
Worry and pain

06:38.983 --> 06:41.975
Is that all you got?
Is that all you got?

06:43.195 --> 06:45.151
Your girlfriend rocks, brah.

06:45.239 --> 06:47.275
Yeah, right?

07:08.053 --> 07:10.260
You won't spoil my day

07:11.015 --> 07:12.755
Give it your best shot

07:13.809 --> 07:15.595
Another hurricane

07:16.562 --> 07:17.722
Is that all you got?

07:20.357 --> 07:22.188
-(BLOWS NOTE)
-What the fuck?

07:24.612 --> 07:26.273
That's Glen's trombone?

07:26.363 --> 07:29.821
How do you happen to have his trombone,
if he isn't under arrest?

07:31.035 --> 07:33.868
Batiste, Antoine.
That's the only guy that we arrested.

07:34.747 --> 07:37.284
Look, if you don't want to represent him,
I can put it back in the locker.

07:37.374 --> 07:38.750
No, no, no. I'll be his lawyer.

07:38.834 --> 07:41.041
So Antoine is at OPP?

07:41.128 --> 07:43.619
No doubt waiting for you to get him his ROR.

07:43.714 --> 07:44.954
When you see him,

07:45.049 --> 07:48.007
tell him from me he might
want to oil that squeaky middle finger of his.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.505
Here, sign.

07:51.722 --> 07:53.303
Thank God for this, at least.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.972
What? I told the guy we'd hold it for him.

07:57.478 --> 08:00.094
You didn't think we'd hold it for him.

08:00.272 --> 08:02.137
So you're telling me you have no record

08:02.232 --> 08:05.395
of any arrest for anyone else
from the Treme memorial?

08:06.111 --> 08:07.487
Arrests?

08:08.155 --> 08:09.361
No.

08:12.368 --> 08:13.357
(GRUNTS)

08:15.454 --> 08:18.161
TABB: The way they came at us,
I thought we were going to jail for sure.

08:18.415 --> 08:20.406
ANDREWS: Yeah, we didn't do nothing.

08:20.501 --> 08:22.787
Glen David, Derrick.

08:22.878 --> 08:25.119
TABB: Hey, Ms. Toni. How you doin'?

08:25.214 --> 08:28.172
-I got a call you were locked up.
-We were.

08:29.259 --> 08:31.045
They didn't send you to jail?

08:31.136 --> 08:34.128
This one asshole who was in charge,
he wanted to lock us up.

08:34.264 --> 08:35.640
But when they got us back to the station,

08:35.724 --> 08:37.965
none of the police that was out there
wanted to sign the papers.

08:38.060 --> 08:40.016
You should have heard David out there.

08:40.104 --> 08:43.267
Well, I told 'em, you don't take
a musician to jail from New Orleans

08:43.357 --> 08:45.097
for playing for another musician.

08:45.192 --> 08:47.148
So you shamed the
New Orleans Police Department

08:47.236 --> 08:48.817
-out of a bad arrest?
-Hey.

08:48.904 --> 08:51.111
Glen, you'd make a hell of a lawyer.

08:51.198 --> 08:53.439
-Come on, I'll give you a ride.
-Ah, thank you.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.320
-(TONl LAUGHS)
-ANDREWS: So you playing trombone now?

08:55.994 --> 08:58.610
l'm serving $28 bowls
of yaka mein to Yankees.

08:58.706 --> 09:01.413
I don't know whether to feel good
about that or guilty.

09:03.377 --> 09:05.709
Position number four. See him?

09:07.548 --> 09:10.460
-Yeah, I see him.
-Third time he's been in this week.

09:10.551 --> 09:13.918
Comes in by himself, eats, watches Gator.

09:14.012 --> 09:16.173
Has a pretty good serial killer vibe.

09:16.265 --> 09:17.926
(CHUCKLES)
He hasn't said shit to me.

09:18.016 --> 09:21.349
Yeah, he comes in here all the time.
He's in love with you. Either you or Chang.

09:21.437 --> 09:23.223
Or either that
or he wants a 10-course threesome.

09:23.313 --> 09:26.976
Well, if you see him waiting outside
holding a roll of duct tape and a Hefty bag,

09:27.067 --> 09:29.274
-you might wanna make a run for it.
-Oh, thanks.

09:29.361 --> 09:32.478
By the way, tomorrow,
bring a change of clothes with you to work.

09:32.573 --> 09:35.360
I'm gonna take you to dinner after.
It's a chef thing.

09:35.451 --> 09:37.191
I'm wearing a jacket,
that should tell you something.

09:37.286 --> 09:39.572
No way. What, it's a funeral?

09:39.663 --> 09:42.075
No. Trust me, you're gonna wanna be there.

09:42.166 --> 09:44.782
I'm going to New Orleans on Wednesday,
I gotta deal with house shit.

09:44.877 --> 09:46.242
You'll be home in time to pack.

09:51.258 --> 09:55.217
-(MUS|C PLAYING)
-All right, there we go. All right. Thank you.

09:58.474 --> 10:01.261
Good reviews so far.

10:01.351 --> 10:02.966
Sales are outpacing your last release.

10:03.061 --> 10:04.892
You should be pleased, Delmond.

10:04.980 --> 10:06.345
Most of the critics are just happy to write

10:06.440 --> 10:08.522
that it's about New Orleans
and to reference Katrina.

10:08.609 --> 10:11.726
Got no clue about the Indians
or what we're trying to do.

10:11.820 --> 10:13.811
-So now it's not enough to get a good review.
-Hi, how are you?

10:13.906 --> 10:16.568
You need the reviewer
to actually understand the work?

10:16.658 --> 10:18.614
-Hey.
-Hey, thanks, brah.

10:18.702 --> 10:21.318
How about the hot apps?
You good with the chicken satay?

10:21.413 --> 10:22.994
Hey, how you doing?

10:23.081 --> 10:25.914
Or did the label screw you on those, too?

10:26.001 --> 10:28.037
-Hey.
-DELMOND: Ah, fuck.

10:28.879 --> 10:30.790
I hear you, man.

10:30.964 --> 10:32.545
It's just that...

10:32.633 --> 10:35.420
I bumped into Wynton
a moment ago at the bar

10:35.511 --> 10:37.627
and he gave me one of them
Wynton compliments, you know?

10:37.721 --> 10:39.882
Called it an "interesting amalgam,

10:40.015 --> 10:42.347
"not quite jazz, but intriguing for what it is."

10:42.434 --> 10:43.594
(CHUCKLES)

10:43.685 --> 10:46.347
Delmond, you told me when you started this,

10:46.438 --> 10:49.020
jazz literati are gonna hate it

10:49.107 --> 10:52.520
almost as much as some of the
Mardi Gras Indians are going to resent it.

10:52.736 --> 10:54.237
Speaking of which,

10:54.321 --> 10:57.154
I thought your father would
come up here for the release.

10:57.241 --> 10:58.947
Now, my father, he's just like,

10:59.034 --> 11:02.117
"Who the hell cares what anybody thinks?"
He can do that.

11:02.329 --> 11:05.196
Matter of fact, the other day, I went with him
to an Indian council meeting

11:05.290 --> 11:08.248
and most of the other chiefs,
they were cool, you know,

11:08.335 --> 11:09.871
but a couple of them
started dogging the music,

11:09.962 --> 11:12.499
saying we were messing with the tradition.
Know what he told them?

11:14.675 --> 11:16.006
(MIMICKING ALBERT)
"Don't listen, then."

11:16.093 --> 11:17.424
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

11:17.511 --> 11:20.469
Swear, man. lwish I could be like that.
The man ain't never soft.

11:20.556 --> 11:21.966
THOMPSON: Delmond, loving the new tracks,

11:22.182 --> 11:24.514
the whole recondite Native American motif.

11:24.601 --> 11:28.594
I mean, seriously, where in your imagination
did all of that come from?

11:30.315 --> 11:31.350
Well, actually...

11:40.534 --> 11:41.774
-Wah!
-(SCREAMS)

11:41.869 --> 11:42.904
(LAUGHS)
Were you there?

11:42.995 --> 11:44.781
Yeah, I saw the first three.

11:44.872 --> 11:48.160
Then I went to '02 and had to start my set.

11:48.250 --> 11:49.865
(LAUGHING)
And?

11:50.127 --> 11:52.459
-You guys killed it!
-What?

11:52.546 --> 11:55.538
-You killed it!
-(KISSES)

11:55.632 --> 11:57.714
Baby, we played Frenchmen Street.

11:57.801 --> 11:58.790
(GRUNTS)

11:58.886 --> 12:01.673
Not on the sidewalk, in a club.

12:01.763 --> 12:02.798
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

12:02.890 --> 12:05.597
-We played two sets at d.b.a.!
-Great, hold on.

12:06.018 --> 12:07.224
Okay, that's better.

12:07.311 --> 12:10.269
And I even wrote a few of those songs.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.431
I am so proud of you.

12:15.861 --> 12:17.476
Well, of course you are.

12:17.571 --> 12:20.904
You are my first groupie, Davis.

12:21.158 --> 12:24.366
And with that honor comes rights

12:24.494 --> 12:26.655
and responsibilities.

12:33.045 --> 12:35.787
It's like 6:00 in the morning.

12:38.050 --> 12:39.506
Tomorrow we play in Morgan City

12:39.593 --> 12:42.881
and then it's back to Lafayette
for more rehearsals.

12:43.263 --> 12:46.255
It's now or never,

12:46.934 --> 12:48.219
sucker

12:48.769 --> 12:49.975
(ANNIE LAUGHS)

12:52.397 --> 12:53.853
-Mom!
-(ALARM CLOCK BEEPING)

12:55.067 --> 12:56.523
-Mama!
-LaDONNA: What?

12:57.444 --> 12:58.945
-Where's my other shoe?
-(TOILET FLUSHES)

12:59.029 --> 13:00.644
-You look under your bed?
-RANDALL: I looked there.

13:00.739 --> 13:03.355
-Alcide, you find your book bag yet?
-No.

13:04.117 --> 13:05.982
Is that my toothbrush?

13:07.245 --> 13:09.827
Damn, boy, find your book bag.

13:10.207 --> 13:11.663
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

13:13.961 --> 13:15.952
-RANDALL: Where was it at?
-Under your bed.

13:16.129 --> 13:17.710
LARRY: LaDonna.

13:17.839 --> 13:18.999
(BEEPING STOPS)

13:21.343 --> 13:24.130
RANDALL: Please?
ALCIDE: No.

13:25.347 --> 13:27.759
RANDALL: Why not?
LaDONNA: Oh, man.

13:29.518 --> 13:30.803
What's up?

13:30.894 --> 13:32.134
Did you fill out that permission slip?

13:32.229 --> 13:33.969
-The one for Randall?
-Oh, shit.

13:34.064 --> 13:35.179
RANDALL: I don't break stuff.

13:35.273 --> 13:36.683
I mean...

13:37.567 --> 13:39.819
Sorry, Victorine.

13:41.405 --> 13:43.441
Living in closer quarters like this,

13:43.699 --> 13:47.317
it would probably be better
if everyone dressed before breakfast.

13:47.411 --> 13:49.697
Victorine, we're all family here.

13:49.788 --> 13:51.744
I don't think she needs you to tell her...

13:51.832 --> 13:54.164
LaDONNA: No. Uh-uh.
She got a point.

13:54.751 --> 13:57.458
Though in this case,
after Larry gets the boys off to school,

13:57.546 --> 13:59.628
I'm going back to bed.

13:59.715 --> 14:02.752
LaDonna closed last night,
didn't get home till 2:00.

14:02.843 --> 14:05.334
Oh, of course. Your bar.

14:05.429 --> 14:07.636
(FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING STAIRS)

14:08.181 --> 14:09.842
We're late. Let's roll.

14:12.269 --> 14:14.225
-Bye, Ma.
-LARRY: She'll sign it tomorrow.

14:14.688 --> 14:16.098
ALCIDE: Bye, Ma.

14:18.442 --> 14:21.058
MAN ON PA: Officer Dalmadge,
please report to the warden's office.

14:21.153 --> 14:24.520
Officer Dalmadge,
please report to the warden's office.

14:27.451 --> 14:31.444
Man, I can't get some of my own people
to make this ride, but here you are.

14:32.456 --> 14:34.993
A friend's a friend. That's my motto.

14:35.083 --> 14:37.460
-That's your motto?
-I got a bunch of mottos.

14:37.544 --> 14:39.626
-(CHUCKLES) Yeah.
-I got mottos for every situation.

14:42.716 --> 14:45.298
-Thirty-seven months, huh?
-Yeah.

14:45.802 --> 14:49.044
Could have got less if you'd have cooperated.
That's what people say.

14:51.308 --> 14:53.139
But you didn't.

14:53.226 --> 14:55.933
So you drove all the way up here
from New Orleans to ask me why...

14:56.021 --> 14:59.013
Flew in from Dallas, actually. I've been home.

14:59.107 --> 15:01.439
All right, flew in from Dallas to Atlanta

15:01.526 --> 15:03.812
to ask poor old incarcerated Oliver Thomas

15:03.904 --> 15:07.738
why he wouldn't drop a dime
when the feds rolled him up, huh?

15:08.075 --> 15:11.067
Well, that, and I want to ride Zulu again.

15:11.161 --> 15:13.527
-(CHUCKLES)
-So I figured I'd ask you about that, too.

15:14.039 --> 15:15.279
Yeah.

15:16.500 --> 15:18.240
You're not cooperating, right?

15:19.961 --> 15:22.373
I guess I just didn't want
to play the game anymore.

15:22.464 --> 15:24.671
And I'll do the time I deserve to do.

15:25.258 --> 15:28.170
'Cause I did what I did, sorry for that.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.676
Let a lot of people down.

15:31.473 --> 15:36.137
As to whoever did what else,
that's between them and their conscience.

15:36.228 --> 15:39.186
MAN ON PA: Officer Dalmadge,
please report to the warden's office.

15:39.272 --> 15:43.311
Be that as it may, I've kept every promise
that I've made to you, Lieutenant.

15:43.401 --> 15:45.187
Yes, sir.

15:45.278 --> 15:47.690
Six months ago, I transferred you to Homicide

15:47.823 --> 15:51.441
with the promise that Captain Guidry
would not be your problem.

15:51.535 --> 15:52.615
Yes, sir.

15:52.702 --> 15:54.784
And in the end,
it's Guidry that we transferred,

15:54.913 --> 15:56.619
and you're still there.

15:57.124 --> 16:00.207
Look, Chief, with all due respect,

16:01.211 --> 16:03.122
if Guidry had been doing his job,

16:03.213 --> 16:06.626
you'd be having this conversation with him
and I'd be out to pasture somewhere.

16:07.634 --> 16:09.465
Well, now it's time to let me go home.

16:09.553 --> 16:11.760
-Back to 8th District.
-Transfer you, too.

16:11.847 --> 16:13.428
That unit is full of Guidry's people.

16:13.515 --> 16:15.301
They resent that he's gone and I'm still there,

16:15.392 --> 16:19.476
and I cannot be effective in that environment.

16:19.938 --> 16:23.305
Says here that your shift's clearance rate
is twice that of the other two.

16:23.400 --> 16:27.518
Deputy, I am requesting a transfer.

16:27.612 --> 16:29.022
Denied.

16:30.740 --> 16:32.731
Terry, I need you where I have you.

16:34.452 --> 16:35.988
All right.

16:36.079 --> 16:38.035
If you want me to stay,

16:39.207 --> 16:40.617
I have one other request.

16:41.418 --> 16:43.750
-Fire away.
-Limit the details.

16:44.880 --> 16:47.997
Make eight hours a week the maximum
amount of secondary employment

16:48.091 --> 16:49.922
for Homicide detectives.

16:50.010 --> 16:52.342
You think the detectives resent you now?

16:52.429 --> 16:55.262
Imagine what it's like
I put a cap on secondary.

16:55.765 --> 16:57.096
But...

16:57.809 --> 17:00.221
Give me a chance to confer
with Captain Hardesty

17:00.312 --> 17:01.722
and the people in legal,

17:01.813 --> 17:04.190
and I'll have an answer for you by week's end.

17:04.274 --> 17:07.107
-l'm off till Friday.
