33:11.490 --> 33:13.026
What's the game nowadays?

33:13.117 --> 33:14.323
NOAH.

33:14.410 --> 33:16.116
Noah? Like the ark?

33:16.203 --> 33:17.443
(SCOFFS)

33:17.538 --> 33:19.199
N-O-A-H.

33:19.290 --> 33:22.373
New Orleans Affordable Homeownership.

33:22.543 --> 33:24.158
What's your contract?

33:24.253 --> 33:25.618
I'm a sub.

33:25.713 --> 33:28.546
Getting what I can
out this Florida lady who got the connect.

33:29.675 --> 33:32.963
Christ, that's half-assed.
Your guys can't do better than that?

33:33.053 --> 33:35.260
Man, I'm demo and hauling, me.

33:35.347 --> 33:39.716
This clever bitch got us out here
pretending to do the work on this one.

33:39.810 --> 33:42.597
Another two,
she ain't got us doing nothing at all.

33:42.855 --> 33:44.311
Pretending?

33:44.398 --> 33:47.265
Cheap door, some paint, cut the grass.

33:47.359 --> 33:48.769
Bullshit only.

33:48.861 --> 33:52.570
You walk inside,
the whole damn place rotted out.

33:52.823 --> 33:55.030
You got a name, address for the lady?

33:55.117 --> 33:57.073
I got an address over on Howard,

33:57.161 --> 33:59.652
but it ain't nothing
but an office with a secretary.

33:59.788 --> 34:01.915
I wanna connect with her,

34:02.541 --> 34:03.826
I call her.

34:05.669 --> 34:08.411
I need to start voting Republican and shit.

34:08.505 --> 34:10.962
-(DIALING)
-Vote your conscience, son.

34:13.719 --> 34:15.300
You got a percentage?

34:15.429 --> 34:16.965
She pay by the house.

34:17.056 --> 34:19.763
With me, you got points. You know that.

34:22.811 --> 34:23.846
(ENGINE STARTS)

34:23.938 --> 34:25.644
Vigilante killings?

34:25.814 --> 34:27.099
In Algiers.

34:27.191 --> 34:30.399
That was the tip, anyway. Shootings of blacks
by white civilians during Katrina.

34:30.486 --> 34:33.444
So you sued the coroner for autopsy reports.
Which ones?

34:33.530 --> 34:36.192
I asked for autopsies
on every death in Orleans Parish

34:36.283 --> 34:38.524
from the date of the levee breaks
until the end of September.

34:38.744 --> 34:39.859
And?

34:39.954 --> 34:41.615
-Dr. Minyard refused.
-(CHUCKLES)

34:41.705 --> 34:43.411
So I filed suit three months ago,

34:43.499 --> 34:46.582
state judge found in our favor
and, eventually,

34:46.669 --> 34:49.285
I get the autopsies
from the time period in question,

34:49.380 --> 34:50.836
except for any deaths

34:50.923 --> 34:53.710
from gunshots,
knife wounds or blunt-force trauma.

34:53.801 --> 34:56.213
What they sent me was whitewashed.

34:56.804 --> 34:59.090
Have you ever been to New Orleans before,
Mr. Everett?

34:59.306 --> 35:00.466
No.

35:01.267 --> 35:03.679
Well, welcome to another world.
(CHUCKLES)

35:08.023 --> 35:09.763
lwas told that I should look you up.

35:09.858 --> 35:13.225
That you've been doing
civil rights work since the '80s.

35:14.113 --> 35:16.274
A long time to be ignored, I know.

35:16.740 --> 35:18.401
Ahem, um...

35:19.410 --> 35:22.698
I'm wondering if you know anyone
in the black community over in Algiers.

35:23.872 --> 35:25.578
I mean, if the coroner won't
give me the autopsies,

35:25.666 --> 35:28.624
there's always another way
to skin the cat, right?

35:28.711 --> 35:32.044
I haven't had a case over there
in a decade, but...

35:32.214 --> 35:35.832
I do know a guy that grew up in the
Fischer Projects over there on the Westbank.

35:35.926 --> 35:37.791
He's a good investigator.

35:37.886 --> 35:38.966
Okay.

35:40.723 --> 35:41.963
I'll have him get in touch with you.

35:42.057 --> 35:44.139
-Thank you so much.
-You bet.

35:46.937 --> 35:48.802
(SONG PLAYING)

35:54.695 --> 35:57.528
That was Benny Spellman's
Lipstick Traces.

35:57.614 --> 35:59.650
Which I wanted to get on today,

35:59.742 --> 36:01.983
because Benny's been ailing since his stroke.

36:02.077 --> 36:05.410
And between y'all and me,
I was hoping that he might be around

36:05.497 --> 36:08.989
to where he be one participating in what
is becoming known around town as

36:09.084 --> 36:10.870
"The Opus Without Pity,"

36:10.961 --> 36:13.122
a work most definitely in progress.

36:13.213 --> 36:14.999
"Oh, no," I hear you saying,

36:15.090 --> 36:18.708
"Davis, please, mother of God, say it isn't so!"

36:22.681 --> 36:23.841
It's so.

36:23.932 --> 36:26.139
I've already signed up A! Johnson,
"Frogman" Henry,

36:26.226 --> 36:28.012
and I'm coming after Benny and Irma next.

36:28.103 --> 36:31.766
Yes, the great voices
of New Orleans' rhythm and blues

36:31.857 --> 36:34.439
will speak to our current
sociopolitical contretemps

36:34.526 --> 36:36.107
in a way that only they can,

36:36.195 --> 36:38.902
making Puccini my bitch in the process.

36:40.115 --> 36:41.366
Hey.

36:41.450 --> 36:44.613
Yes, music lovers,
"Katrina: An Opera in Blues and Funk."

36:44.745 --> 36:46.531
And to help fund this essential project,

36:46.622 --> 36:48.988
please allow me to shill
for my other current endeavor,

36:49.083 --> 36:51.199
McAlary's Musical Heritage Tours,

36:51.293 --> 36:52.999
Tuesdays and Thursdays, noon and 3:00.

36:53.087 --> 36:54.873
Starting on Rampart and Dumaine.

36:54.963 --> 36:56.544
All proceeds benefiting the opera.

36:56.632 --> 36:58.418
So please tell your friends, tell your family,

36:58.509 --> 37:01.251
but most importantly, tell the tourists.

37:07.142 --> 37:10.225
Okay, well, I'm DJ Davis

37:10.437 --> 37:13.053
sitting in for Judy Wood on the day shift.

37:13.148 --> 37:16.015
We have a fresh release
from Delmond Lambreaux

37:16.151 --> 37:18.813
and his father Big Chief Albert Lambreaux
of the Guardians,

37:18.904 --> 37:22.738
taking that Indian thing
to where it never dared go before.

37:24.827 --> 37:26.363
(SONG PLAYING)

37:29.665 --> 37:31.201
(HAMMERING)

37:37.005 --> 37:39.132
(POWER SAW WHIRRING)

37:45.848 --> 37:47.554
(SONG PLAYING ON RADIO)

37:55.315 --> 37:56.930
You know who y'all listening to?

37:58.193 --> 37:59.182
Que?

37:59.653 --> 38:01.518
On that radio there.

38:04.324 --> 38:05.860
Turn that up.

38:10.247 --> 38:12.238
(VOLUME INCREASES)

38:14.042 --> 38:15.498
That's me!

38:16.295 --> 38:17.626
Right there!

38:17.713 --> 38:19.123
Ese viejo esta loco.

38:19.214 --> 38:20.294
(LAUGHS)

38:20.382 --> 38:21.792
"Loco," shit!

38:21.884 --> 38:25.172
That's me on your radio.
And that right there?

38:26.513 --> 38:28.469
(TRUMPET PLAYING)

38:28.557 --> 38:30.673
That's my son on that horn.

38:30.767 --> 38:32.428
(LAUGHS)

38:32.519 --> 38:34.055
(COUGHS)

38:39.318 --> 38:42.776
Sonny, you come for dinner tonight?

38:42.905 --> 38:44.486
Well, actually...

38:48.076 --> 38:51.534
Actually, lwas thinking
I might take Linh to this restaurant...

38:51.747 --> 38:53.954
Real nice place. Clancy's.

38:54.041 --> 38:56.532
-In New Orleans?
-Yeah, uptown.

38:56.710 --> 38:58.291
It's a real nice place. Ijust thought...

38:58.378 --> 39:01.461
No, no, no. It too long to ride to New Orleans.

39:01.965 --> 39:03.000
It 5:00 now.

39:03.091 --> 39:06.800
By the time you change your clothes,
get clean and go, you have no time.

39:07.346 --> 39:10.429
You have to bring Linh right back. Crazy.

39:10.933 --> 39:13.470
Mr. Tran. Linh, me,

39:13.560 --> 39:15.096
we've been going out for months now.

39:15.187 --> 39:18.224
Okay, for you tonight, restaurant, okay?

39:18.315 --> 39:20.647
Dong Phuong. I treat.

39:25.697 --> 39:27.608
I'm saying they locked me up, too,

39:27.991 --> 39:29.606
and nobody even know.

39:29.701 --> 39:30.816
Ain't that a mess?

39:30.911 --> 39:33.698
You gonna sit there and pout,
because Glen David and Derrick

39:33.789 --> 39:36.622
took a charge for playing in the street
and no one talking about you? For real?

39:36.792 --> 39:37.872
I'm just saying.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.370
Well, I'm just saying,

39:39.461 --> 39:43.374
Glen and Derrick, they ain't neither of them
the assistant band director at Elie.

39:43.465 --> 39:45.251
And how you think it would
look to the school

39:45.342 --> 39:48.926
if you got locked up for giving the finger
to the police all disorderly-like?

39:49.263 --> 39:51.720
Don't look now, Antoine,
but you becoming a grown-up.

39:51.807 --> 39:52.796
(SCOFFS)

39:52.891 --> 39:54.506
And you need
to be carrying it like a grown-up.

39:54.601 --> 39:58.139
I ain't no grown-up.
I'm a musician, God damn it.

39:58.313 --> 39:59.473
Oh, yeah.

40:00.691 --> 40:03.603
BARACK OBAMA ON TV:
...because the legacy of their sacrifice...

40:04.903 --> 40:08.395
You know, Glen, Derrick and the Fraziers?

40:08.532 --> 40:10.818
They're gonna be in the Treme
tomorrow night

40:10.909 --> 40:12.240
and playing for Ken/vin again.

40:12.327 --> 40:13.783
DESIREE: You ain't gonna be there.

40:13.870 --> 40:15.121
Desiree.

40:15.205 --> 40:18.197
You the assistant band director.
You making a steady wage.

40:18.292 --> 40:21.079
You ain't getting locked up, Antoine.
(HUFFS)

40:22.629 --> 40:24.085
(MUTTERS)

40:24.172 --> 40:27.380
Get my ass locked up
any damn time I feel like it.

40:27.843 --> 40:29.128
Yeah.

40:29.469 --> 40:32.632
America had not made the right choice
over the easy choice.

40:37.477 --> 40:39.183
Mark's a good guy.

40:41.148 --> 40:43.013
Boys and him get along?

40:43.483 --> 40:45.860
Yeah, they're fine.

40:48.196 --> 40:51.279
So... Colts are looking good this year.

40:51.366 --> 40:52.355
(KAY SCOFFS)

40:53.827 --> 40:56.193
And you got that car race, right?

40:58.373 --> 41:00.864
So how's the sorghum coming in?

41:00.959 --> 41:03.792
Come on, it's a place like any other.

41:05.297 --> 41:08.004
You never really took to New Orleans.

41:08.925 --> 41:11.052
Even before the flood.

41:11.261 --> 41:12.637
Didn't work for you, did it?

41:14.056 --> 41:15.341
Dreamers.

41:15.807 --> 41:17.422
Dreamers and drunks.

41:18.977 --> 41:20.433
I don't think I'm either.

41:20.520 --> 41:23.387
Well, maybe you're in the wrong place, then.

41:24.274 --> 41:25.775
Listen, Terry,

41:26.777 --> 41:28.438
I've been thinking that,

41:28.528 --> 41:31.656
until you're out of that trailer
and back in your house,

41:31.740 --> 41:33.856
I don't think the boys
should be staying there.

41:33.950 --> 41:36.817
Why not? It's a trailer.

41:36.912 --> 41:39.324
It's like camping out or something.

41:39.414 --> 41:40.950
I saw a report

41:41.041 --> 41:44.033
that all the FEMA trailers have formaldehyde.

41:44.336 --> 41:46.622
People are getting sick, Terry.

41:51.134 --> 41:53.341
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

42:02.938 --> 42:04.098
Sonny.

42:07.776 --> 42:09.516
You need to drive back now?

42:09.611 --> 42:12.273
It's crazy. Living in another century.

42:13.573 --> 42:15.985
It's very different for you, I know.

42:16.076 --> 42:18.488
If I don't get you back home in like an hour,

42:18.578 --> 42:21.866
he'll get back in that car,
start rolling around the village looking for me.

42:21.957 --> 42:23.288
An hour after that,

42:23.375 --> 42:27.618
every able-bodied Vietnamese fisherman
in Versailles will be hunting us.

42:30.841 --> 42:32.081
(HORN HONKS)

42:43.520 --> 42:45.806
Go to the canal? See the birds?

42:46.273 --> 42:48.013
That was last night.

42:48.775 --> 42:50.640
Let's go down Chef Menteur.

42:50.736 --> 42:52.317
We can watch the traffic light change.

42:52.404 --> 42:53.393
(LAUGHS)

43:00.036 --> 43:01.572
(BOTH PANTING)

43:06.835 --> 43:09.167
Don't say anything.

43:10.130 --> 43:11.119
(CHUCKLES)

43:14.426 --> 43:16.667
Well, I'm not going to think.
(GIGGLES)

43:18.513 --> 43:21.380
There will be no thinking.

43:23.143 --> 43:25.885
We can talk about work.

43:28.356 --> 43:31.598
You could tell me about your adventures
in New York.

43:31.693 --> 43:32.978
We could.

43:33.653 --> 43:35.484
But I'm not going to.

43:36.865 --> 43:39.197
I just want to lay around.

43:44.581 --> 43:46.367
When's your flight?

43:47.042 --> 43:48.578
8:00 tomorrow.

43:56.885 --> 43:59.547
-I like it.
-You got used to wearing it long.

43:59.638 --> 44:02.550
Yeah, I'm glad we decided to keep it.

44:02.641 --> 44:06.099
-Sofia? Did you like what we did last time?
-Sure.

44:07.020 --> 44:10.228
Do you think you could make it
so it's kind of not a hairstyle?

44:10.816 --> 44:12.226
Excuse me?

44:12.317 --> 44:13.432
SOFIA: Something that says,

44:13.527 --> 44:16.564
"I'm not styling my hair. Ijust am."
You know?

44:17.155 --> 44:19.646
Like, "This is me just hanging out,

44:19.741 --> 44:22.858
"not pretending to anything
other than what's real."

44:22.953 --> 44:26.571
Well, well.
That coffee shop must be deep in the Bywater.

44:26.665 --> 44:28.701
It's worse than that, Jay.

44:28.792 --> 44:31.579
Her boyfriend's a musician down there.

44:31.670 --> 44:33.877
Oh, God. Sofia Bernette?

44:34.297 --> 44:36.003
-Bywater crusty.
-(TONI CHUCKLES)

44:36.925 --> 44:38.506
I'll bet you've been shopping
at all the vintage stores.

44:38.593 --> 44:40.709
Up and down Decatur Street.

44:41.429 --> 44:45.547
Some nights she goes out dressed like
something out of a Steinbeck novel.

44:45.642 --> 44:47.223
Thanks, Heather.

44:47.352 --> 44:48.853
Have you met him?

44:48.937 --> 44:52.304
No, I keep stopping in for coffee,
hoping to catch a glimpse,

44:52.524 --> 44:54.890
but so far I've been shutout.

44:55.944 --> 44:57.809
When are you having him to dinner, Sof?

44:57.904 --> 45:00.520
When I'm 30, maybe.

45:02.576 --> 45:03.565
(CHUCKLES)

45:07.372 --> 45:09.237
Okay, gather close.

45:12.210 --> 45:16.579
I'm DJ Davis,
and today's musical heritage tour

45:16.673 --> 45:18.413
begins on hallowed ground.

45:19.551 --> 45:22.258
-J&M Record Shop.
-(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

45:22.345 --> 45:25.007
Cosimo Matassa opened
a studio here in the '40s,

45:30.520 --> 45:35.514
This place turned out more hits
than any other studio in the country.

45:35.650 --> 45:37.106
Good Rockin' Tonight,

45:37.193 --> 45:39.024
all the Fats Domino stuff,

45:39.112 --> 45:41.774
Little Richard, Ray Charles...

45:41.865 --> 45:43.696
It's a Laundromat.

45:44.492 --> 45:45.618
Clearly.

45:45.702 --> 45:47.408
But when you go inside

45:47.495 --> 45:49.531
and you stand next to the change machine,

45:50.874 --> 45:52.489
you are more or less on the spot

45:52.584 --> 45:55.826
where Earl Palmer laid down
the backbeat that changed the world.

45:55.921 --> 45:58.003
But it's just a laundry now.

45:58.131 --> 46:00.213
With a built-in daiquiri stand.

46:00.300 --> 46:01.585
Questions? No? Great.

46:01.676 --> 46:04.133
Let's cross the threshold and partake.

46:10.185 --> 46:11.470
(LAUGHING)

46:15.523 --> 46:17.514
-Look who needs a trim.
-Hey.

46:17.609 --> 46:19.099
-I got all the trim I need.
-(PATRONS LAUGH)

46:19.194 --> 46:21.810
Hey, what up, Anthony?
How you moms and them, man?

46:21.905 --> 46:23.645
We'd complain, but who would listen?

46:23.740 --> 46:25.355
ALL: Yeah. All right.

46:25.450 --> 46:27.566
This is my friend Louis.
Louis, meet the wise men of Algiers.

46:27.744 --> 46:28.779
How's it going, guys?

46:28.870 --> 46:30.952
ANTHONY: Don't nothing happen
this crew don't know about.

46:31.039 --> 46:34.452
Okay, do me a favor, though.
Call me L.P. I don't really like Louis.

46:34.542 --> 46:36.828
-Ah, no problem, Lou.
-(PATRONS LAUGH)

46:37.879 --> 46:40.291
Don't get to harvest
that kind of crop too often.

46:40.382 --> 46:41.542
Right.

46:41.716 --> 46:43.217
So how about them 'aints?

46:43.468 --> 46:45.004
ALL: (GROANING) Oh, man.

46:45.095 --> 46:46.631
Same old Saints, man.

46:46.721 --> 46:50.054
-Yeah, the Saints for lack of season.
-I don't know.

46:50.433 --> 46:52.264
Nice to meet you.

46:52.394 --> 46:54.009
(ALL CHATTERING)

46:54.813 --> 46:56.895
Holding the breeze by every one of them.

46:57.649 --> 47:01.392
Gaze, if you will,
at the grounds of Armstrong Park,

47:01.486 --> 47:04.444
home to Congo Square,

47:04.614 --> 47:06.320
where, basically,

47:06.408 --> 47:09.491
any American music
worth talking about comes from.

47:10.996 --> 47:13.988
Syncopated rhythms, call and response,

47:14.082 --> 47:16.619
the blue notes of West African slaves

47:16.751 --> 47:18.491
commingling on market days

47:18.586 --> 47:22.329
with the brass instrumentation
of the European musical heritage.

47:22.424 --> 47:25.086
Ladies and gentlemen, I give you

47:26.219 --> 47:28.676
the birthplace ofjazz!

47:30.765 --> 47:32.756
Why don't we go there?

47:32.851 --> 47:34.682
Closed since the storm.

47:34.811 --> 47:37.928
You mean they can't manage
to clean up a park after two years?

47:38.023 --> 47:40.230
Dude, two years is but a

47:40.567 --> 47:42.398
twinkle in the eye of our civic leaders.

47:42.485 --> 47:43.816
We've only got a marker

47:43.903 --> 47:46.861
in the general vicinity
of Buddy Bolden's grave a few years back,

47:46.948 --> 47:48.813
and he's been gone
for more than half a century.

47:49.617 --> 47:50.948
So... Questions?

47:51.870 --> 47:53.781
Good. Let's sojourn uptown.

47:54.664 --> 47:56.120
(MUSIC PLAYING)

48:07.302 --> 48:09.008
Ms. Mortensen?

48:09.095 --> 48:11.882
-Nelson Hidalgo. Dallas, Texas.
-Nelson.

48:11.973 --> 48:15.591
You ever been here?
You sit, drink, and the bar spins.

48:15.685 --> 48:17.641
For real, once around every half hour.

48:17.729 --> 48:19.720
Are you with the government, Mr. Hidalgo?

48:20.607 --> 48:22.643
Do I look like I'm government?

48:23.526 --> 48:25.482
Are you with the RNC, then?

48:25.612 --> 48:28.570
(CHUCKLES) I paid those dues in Texas.

48:28.656 --> 48:31.147
Just like you paid them in Florida, I'm sure.

48:31.284 --> 48:33.070
It's a big swing state, Florida.

48:33.161 --> 48:34.401
Come on, sit, have a drink.

48:34.496 --> 48:38.330
So you're not with the government
and you're not from New Orleans.

48:40.710 --> 48:43.122
I'm a contractor, just like you.

48:43.213 --> 48:46.705
Right, then why do I need to know you,
Mr. Hidalgo?

48:50.470 --> 48:51.459
(CHUCKLES)

48:53.848 --> 48:57.432
And here we have the most important row

48:57.519 --> 49:00.101
ofjazz landmarks left on earth.

49:00.188 --> 49:03.430
Starting here, the Eagle Saloon,

49:03.566 --> 49:06.774
where Louis Armstrong's career began.

49:06.861 --> 49:09.773
He won a talent show here when he was a kid.

49:09.864 --> 49:12.276
He won that at the Iroquois Theater.

49:12.408 --> 49:14.694
No, I'm pretty sure it was here at the Eagle.

49:14.869 --> 49:17.736
That was when he put on make-up
and performed in whiteface.

49:17.831 --> 49:19.037
That was a theater.

49:19.124 --> 49:21.456
Why would there be
a children's talent show at a saloon?

49:21.543 --> 49:23.408
Oh, that's no problem in New Orleans.

49:23.628 --> 49:25.789
Kids in bars is one of our sacred traditions.

49:25.880 --> 49:27.461
This says it was the Iroquois Theater.

49:27.549 --> 49:29.039
DAVIS: In any event!

49:29.217 --> 49:32.050
This area was called "Back 0' Town."

49:32.137 --> 49:35.425
Armstrong grew up on Perdido Street

49:35.557 --> 49:38.799
over there in a house

49:38.893 --> 49:41.054
that we tore down in the '60s.

49:42.063 --> 49:45.555
Did you people ever actually preserve
anything of note?

49:48.903 --> 49:50.985
-Preservation Hall.
-When was that founded?

49:51.072 --> 49:53.313
'60, '61, maybe?

49:54.325 --> 49:56.862
Really? That far back?

49:58.246 --> 49:59.702
Come on, son, this is bullshit.

50:01.583 --> 50:03.824
Ridiculous. Wanker.

50:11.176 --> 50:12.632
(CAR REMOTE CHIRPS)

50:33.531 --> 50:34.816
(SNIFFING)

50:54.886 --> 50:58.595
Alcide, darling, I think you left
your salad fork in the potato server.

51:06.189 --> 51:07.679
You know, where I was raised,

51:07.774 --> 51:09.435
in the 6th Ward,

51:10.151 --> 51:14.144
we were taught that it was bad manners
to correct a guest for their manners.

51:14.239 --> 51:18.403
If they picked up the wrong fork
or poured beer into the wine glass,

51:18.826 --> 51:20.487
we were supposed to do the same.

51:21.996 --> 51:26.330
But in no way would we
be treating LaDonna like a guest.

51:26.918 --> 51:27.907
Oh.

51:28.836 --> 51:30.417
I'm family.

51:32.173 --> 51:33.879
All right, then.

51:34.968 --> 51:36.504
Since I'm kin,

51:37.303 --> 51:42.138
I ain't gonna pay no never mind
to how I'm supposed to do.

51:43.476 --> 51:46.388
I'm guessing you don't have no malt liquor.

51:47.105 --> 51:48.891
Nothing in a 40, huh?

51:50.191 --> 51:52.273
Maybe you got a paper bag?

51:52.360 --> 51:54.066
'Cause I'm thinking
about finishing this here up

51:54.153 --> 51:56.109
on the "cornder."

51:56.239 --> 51:57.979
(RANDALL AND ALCIDE CHUCKLE)

52:00.660 --> 52:02.070
Excuse me.

52:07.542 --> 52:09.908
LARRY: (WHISPERING)
You are not helping.

52:10.336 --> 52:13.043
(WHISPERING)
Me? What did I do?

52:13.131 --> 52:14.291
(LARRY SIGHS)

52:17.135 --> 52:20.673
Baby, I'm doing everything I can
to find a house for us.

52:21.055 --> 52:23.967
What about that one up off City Park?

52:24.058 --> 52:26.765
Not enough room for both boys
and my practice.

52:26.894 --> 52:28.475
One bedroom shy.

52:29.314 --> 52:33.227
Another month or two of this shit
and I really will go ghetto.

52:33.318 --> 52:35.855
LaDonna will choke a bitch.

52:35.945 --> 52:36.934
(CHUCKLES)

52:37.739 --> 52:38.728
(CHUCKLES)

52:40.074 --> 52:41.575
Yeah, I know.

52:45.330 --> 52:47.241
So go talk to the guy.

52:48.916 --> 52:52.374
No way. I don't know him.
What if he's a perv?

52:52.462 --> 52:54.578
Or worse, what if he's a food blogger?

52:54.756 --> 52:58.089
He's not. He's one of yours.
He's from New Orleans.

52:58.176 --> 53:00.041
And like others before him,

53:00.136 --> 53:03.799
he's come to poach my prize cook
and offer fame and fortune back home.

53:03.890 --> 53:05.175
So go talk to the mook.

53:05.266 --> 53:07.222
I can't handle the suspense.

53:22.658 --> 53:24.489
I'm not interested. Sorry.

53:27.705 --> 53:29.115
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

53:29.582 --> 53:31.083
(DRUMROLL)

53:31.167 --> 53:33.078
(MUSICIANS WARMING UP)

53:36.339 --> 53:38.625
Keep your eyes open. Keep in touch.

53:47.475 --> 53:49.511
-MAN 1: What's up, son?
-(MAN 2 LAUGHS)

53:55.149 --> 53:56.685
(WATER RUNNING)

53:59.445 --> 54:00.560
(RUNNING STOPS)

54:04.117 --> 54:05.653
Hey, Pop.

54:05.743 --> 54:08.530
See you got the cabinets up
without me, huh?

54:08.621 --> 54:10.327
Finished the plumbing, so...

54:10.415 --> 54:12.906
Hey, read some of these reviews.
They're strong for the most part.

54:13.000 --> 54:14.285
You should have been at the CD launch.

54:14.377 --> 54:16.242
The label actually threw a pretty good party.

54:16.337 --> 54:19.044
Donald was there, Terence, Wynton.

54:19.132 --> 54:22.920
Well, that's your bag.
Gimme a hand with this door to the bathroom.

54:23.010 --> 54:25.217
Come on, now, you're not proud?

54:25.304 --> 54:29.263
I get them lighting fixtures up
in them bedrooms, I'll be proud.

54:29.642 --> 54:32.258
You know, Wynton said it was pretty good,

54:32.353 --> 54:33.854
but it wasn't reallyjazz.

54:33.938 --> 54:35.894
Wynton would say that.

54:36.107 --> 54:39.474
But he don't get the last damn word
on what's jazz and what ain't.

54:39.861 --> 54:41.351
I been listening to and loving jazz

54:41.446 --> 54:44.529
since before that boy was
a thought in Ellis's mind.

54:46.117 --> 54:47.698
If he gave them songs even half a listen,

54:47.785 --> 54:51.152
he'd know that you and me done
broke some fresh fucking ground.

54:51.247 --> 54:53.863
Them songs are gonna stand, son.

54:58.337 --> 55:00.794
(WHISTLES)
Let's get this thing started, man.

55:00.882 --> 55:02.497
I hope y'all got that bail money ready.

55:02.592 --> 55:04.173
Can't tell the sheriff I only got eight.

55:04.260 --> 55:05.466
What's up, man? Hey.

55:05.553 --> 55:07.885
How about Just a Little While?

55:08.055 --> 55:09.556
(MUSICIANS PLAYING)

55:21.652 --> 55:26.021
(SINGING) Just a little while to wait

55:26.115 --> 55:30.950
Just a little while to labor

55:31.037 --> 55:34.404
On the path that's always straight

55:35.791 --> 55:37.327
Just a little more...

55:37.418 --> 55:39.409
(SIREN WAILS)

55:43.174 --> 55:45.665
-Whoa.
-(CROWD COMPLAINING)

55:47.261 --> 55:49.126
Which way you walking?

55:49.222 --> 55:50.632
We going down St. Philip,

55:50.723 --> 55:53.760
all the way to St. Claude,
around Ursulines to Robertson.

55:53.851 --> 55:55.466
Okay, we your escort.

55:55.645 --> 55:57.761
-MAN: AII right.
-(CROWD CHEERING)

55:58.606 --> 56:01.268
Taylor was right, I guess you did shame them.

56:01.692 --> 56:04.229
(MUSICIANS PLAYING)

56:40.314 --> 56:41.303
(SIGHS)

56:47.655 --> 56:49.020
Roast beef.

56:49.991 --> 56:51.322
You?

56:51.409 --> 56:52.899
Oyster, me.

56:57.290 --> 56:58.996
Don't ever change.

57:00.001 --> 57:01.491
Of course not.
